The conformational analysis of 1, 3 and 6 was performed using HyperChem software (HyperChem™ Professional 8.0.7, Hypercube, Inc., Gainesville, FL, 
USA
) under molecular mechanics force field through the Monte Carlo simulation protocol. Selected conformers with Boltzmann distribution higher than 10% distribution were optimized using the density functional theory (DFT) at the B3LYP/6-311G (d) basis set (

). The ECD calculations were carried out by Gaussian 09 software with the time-dependent density functional theory (TD-DFT) method using CAM-B3LYP/6–311++G (d,p) and the Conductor-like Polarizable Continuum Model (C-PCM) was used for solvent effects (CHCl 
3
and MeOH for ECD calculations) (

; 

; 

). The calculated ECD spectra were generated by the GaussSum program.

Colorless needle crystals of 13 were obtained in MeOH: H 
2
O (20:1 v/ v). The diffraction data were integrated using SAINT (Bruker-AXS, 2000). The multiscan absorption corrections were conducted using the SADABS program (

). The structure was solved by intrinsic phasing using SHELXT (Apex2 program suite) (

) and refined by the full-matrix least-squares methods using SHELXTL (

), with the ShelXle user interface (

). All non-hydrogen atoms were refined anisotropically while the H-atoms were located on calculated positions. The crystallographic data was deposited with CCDC No. 2000936. These data can be obtained free of charge from the Cambridge Crystallographic Data Centre (CCDC) via http://www.ccdc.cam.ac.uk/data_request/cif.
